The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Two doubles in the same innings 
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Two doubles in the same innings 
                            
	Gautam Gambhir and V.V.S. Laxman hit double hundreds on Day II of the third Test at the Kotla on Thursday. The following is a list of instances when two batsmen have scored doubles in one Test innings:               
	 D. Bradman (244) and W.H. Ponsford (266), Aus v Eng (The Oval) 1934         
	 S.G. Barnes (234) and D. Bradman (234), Aus v Eng (Sydney) 1946-47         
	 C.C. Hunte (260) and G. Sobers (365*), WI v Pak (Kingston) 1957-58         
	 W.M. Lawry (210) and R.B. Simpson (201), Aus v WI (Bridgetown) 1964-65         
	 M. Nazar (231) and J. Miandad (280*), Pak v Ind (Hyderabad, Pak) 1982-83         
	 G. Fowler (201) and M. Gatting (207), Eng v Ind (Madras) 1984-85         
	 Q. Omar (206) and J. Miandad (203*), Pak v SL (Faisalabad) 1985-86         
	 S. Jayasuriya (340) and R. Mahanama (225), SL v Ind (Colombo, RPS) 1997-98         
	 I. Ahmed (213) and I. Haq (200*), Pak v SL (Dhaka) 1998-99         
	 M. Atapattu (249) and K. Sangakkara (270), SL v Zim (Bulawayo) 2003-04         
	 W. Hinds (213) and S. Chanderpaul (203*), WI v SA (Georgetown) 2004-05         
	 K. Sangakkara (287) and M. Jayawardene (374), SL v SA (Colombo, SSC) 2006         
	 N. McKenzie (226) and G. Smith (232), SA v Ban (Chittagong, DS) 2007-08         
	 G. Gambhir (206) and V.V.S. Laxman (200*), Ind v Aus (Delhi) 2008-09               
